## 1. [Tags & Macros](#1-tags--macros)  

#### 1.1. [Tags](#1-1-tags)  

- Purpose: Tags are an essential Gravwell concept. Every entry has a single tag associated with it; these tags allow us to separate and categorize data at a basic level.  
- [Documentation](<https://docs.gravwell.io/ingesters/ingesters.html#tags>)  
- The Auth0 Kit for Gravwell makes use of the following tags:  
- Total: ***1***  
    - auth0: Tag used for all Auth0 data; necessary for any queries within the Gravwell Auth0 Kit to run properly for dashboards, query library, and templates.  
        - Usage: ``tag=auth0``  

#### 1.2. [Autoextractors](#1-2-autoextractors)  

- Purpose: Autoextractors are simply definitions that can be applied to tags and describe how to correctly extract fields from the data in a given tag. The *ax* module then automatically invokes the appropriate functionality of other modules.  
- [Documentation](<https://docs.gravwell.io/configuration/autoextractors.html>)  
- The Auth0 Kit for Gravwell makes use of the following autoextractors:  
- Total: ***1***  
    - auth0: Gravwell-generated EVs extraction for tag=auth0  

#### 1.3. [Macros](#1-3-macros)  

- Purpose: Search macros are a powerful feature that can help you use Gravwell more effectively. Macros can turn long, repetitive search queries into easily-remembered shortcuts.  
- [Documentation](<https://docs.gravwell.io/search/macros.html>)  
- The Auth0 Kit for Gravwell makes use of the following macros:  
- Total: ***5***  
    - $AUTH0: Configuration Macro; Tag used for all Duo data; necessary for any queries within the Gravwell Duo Kit to run properly for dashboards, query library, and templates.  
    - $AUTH0\_AUTH: This macro aliases eventType (after extraction from type) to eventCode, performs a lookup against Auth0 Event Types, and filters only on events that are categorically "Authentication" based events.  
    - $AUTH0\_AUTH\_CATEGORY: This macro is to be used in conjunction with $AUTH0\_AUTH.  
    - $AUTH0\_EVENT\_LOOKUP: This macro aliases eventType (after extraction from type) to eventCode, and performs a lookup against the Auth0 Event Types Resource (auth0\_eventTypes).  
    - $AUTH0\_FILTER\_CATEGORY: This macro aliases eventType (after extraction from type) to eventCode, performs a lookup against Auth0 Event Types, and then creates a new Enumerated Value (EV) named filterCategory based on the available Auth0 Log Filters referenced below.  

